# indices for positives and negatives
idx_positives = np.arange(length_positives[0])
idx_negatives = np.arange(length_negatives[0])

# shuffle indices
[np.random.shuffle(i) for i in [idx_positives, idx_negatives]]

# TEST set is 10% of positives and same number from negatives
# VALIDATION set is 10% of each (can subsample validation_negatives later)
_10p = int(length_positives[0]/10)
_10n = int(length_negatives[0]/10)

idx_test_p = idx_positives[:_10p]
idx_valid_p = idx_positives[_10p:_10p*2]
idx_train_p = idx_positives[_10p*2:]

idx_test_n = idx_negatives[:_10p]
idx_valid_n= idx_negatives[_10p:_10p+_10n]
idx_train_n = idx_negatives[_10p+_10n:]

idxs = np.array(idx_train_n)
idxs = np.array_split(idxs, N)

n_train = [np.zeros(shape=(i.shape[0],30,23), dtype=np.int8) for i in idxs]

    n_train[i], n_filenames[i] = store_data_numpy(n)

from keras import regularizers

### load model ###

# read model file
json_file = open("../models/deep_model.json", "r")
json_model = json_file.read()
json_file.close()

# load model into keras
model = model_from_json(json_model)

# load weights into model
model.load_weights("../models/deep_model.h5")

# Test the model
y_hat = model.predict(X_valid.reshape( np.insert(X_valid.shape, 3, 1) ))
print('ROC_AUC validation (including more negatives than positives): {:.2f}'.format(roc_auc_score(y_valid, y_hat)))

plt.figure(figsize(14,14))
for n, name in enumerate(['gal4', 'gcn4', 'ino2', 'met4', 'pdr1', 'rtg3', 'hap4', 'mtf1_fly', 'rap1']):

    # read files into lists
    seq = read_fasta('../data/'+ name + '.fasta')
    ss = read_horiz('../data/'+ name + '.horiz')
    
    if name in ['pdr1', 'rtg3', 'hap4']:
        ss = ss[60:-60]
        
    # one hot encode the data
    vars()[name] = prepare_ohe([seq,ss])
    
    # plot predictions
    plt.subplot(3,3,n+1)
    plt.title(name)
    tmp = np.convolve(predict_TAD(eval(name), model), np.ones(20)/20, 'same')
    tmp = np.array([i if i>0.5 else 0 for i in tmp])
    plt.fill_between(np.arange(len(tmp)), tmp, alpha=0.4)
    
    # plot published tADs
    for i in known_regions[name]:
        plt.fill_between(i,np.zeros(len(i)), np.ones(len(i)), color='y', alpha=0.3)
        
    # plot legend 
    if n==2:
        plt.legend(['predictions', 'documented TAD regions'], bbox_to_anchor=(2.2, 0.8), fontsize=15)

display(Markdown("#### Left and center plots show GFP positive or negative reads (y-axis) and the protein positions (x-axis)" \
                 "for two TFs from the 180 TF in Stark's dataset. R:Pearson; Sr=Spearman"))

windows = Stark_data_annotations.values

corrs = np.array([spearmanr(gfp_p[w[0]:w[1]], gfp_m[w[0]:w[1]])[0] for w in windows])
Rs = np.array([np.corrcoef(gfp_p[w[0]:w[1]], gfp_m[w[0]:w[1]])[0][1] for w in windows])

spls=[10, 82]

plt.figure(figsize=(17,5))

for n,j in enumerate(spls):
    
    plt.subplot(1,3,n+1)
    plt.plot(gfp_p[windows[j,0]:windows[j,1]])
    plt.plot(gfp_m[windows[j,0]:windows[j,1]])
    plt.legend(['GFP_plus', 'GFP_minus'])
    plt.ylabel('reads')
    plt.xlabel('protein residue #')
    
    R = np.corrcoef(gfp_p[windows[j,0]:windows[j,1]], 
                    gfp_m[windows[j,0]:windows[j,1]])[0][1]
    
    Sr = spearmanr(gfp_p[windows[j,0]:windows[j,1]], 
                   gfp_m[windows[j,0]:windows[j,1]])[0]
    
    label = 'R={:.3f}\nSr={:.3f}\n'.format(R,Sr)
    plt.title(f[j]+'\n'+label)

special_positions = np.array([18,  68,  75,  77,  82, 144, 151, 154]) # best TADs from Stark's data
superSpecial_positions = np.array([68, 82, 154]) # Very best TADs from Stark's data

# names of special TADs
Special = [f[i] for i in special_positions]
superSpecial = [f[i] for i in superSpecial_positions]

# null hypothesis with the new data
plt.figure(figsize=(15,15))

# set p_dict outside of the loop since this is the most time consuming step
p_dict = make_p_dict(Stark_data_annotations, model)

# set parameters and variables to model different null distributions
MINIMUM_READS = 200
cutoffs = np.hstack([np.linspace(0.5,1.3,20), np.linspace(1.3,5,20) ])

# arrays to store results
Rs = np.zeros(shape=(len(cutoffs), 3)) # 3 for 1-whole dataset, 2-Special, 3-superSpecial
Ss = Rs.copy()
p_valuesR = Rs.copy()
p_valuesS = Rs.copy()


# proceed with measuring p-values under different thresholds
for n,FOLD_CHANGE_THRESHOLD in enumerate(cutoffs):
    
    # generate tables of measurements and predictions for genes in Stark data
    m_dict = make_m_dict(Stark_data_annotations, gfp_p, gfp_m, MINIMUM_READS=MINIMUM_READS, FOLD_CHANGE_THRESHOLD=FOLD_CHANGE_THRESHOLD)
    
    R_tmp = np.zeros(len(f))
    S_tmp = np.zeros(len(f))
    for nk,k in enumerate(f):
        p = np.convolve([i if i>0.5 else 0 for i in p_dict[k]], np.ones(10)/10, 'same') + 10e-4
        m = m_dict[k][:-30] + 10e-4

        # Include here the three Rs: 1-whole dataset, 2-Special, 3-superSpecial
        R_tmp[nk] = np.corrcoef(m,p)[0][1] 
        S_tmp[nk] = spearmanr(m,p)[0]  
    
    # fill array results with pearson (R) and spearman(S) for the 3 cases: all data, special and superSpecial
    Rs[n,0] = np.mean( np.nan_to_num(R_tmp) )
    Rs[n,1] = np.mean( np.nan_to_num(R_tmp[special_positions]) )
    Rs[n,2] = np.mean( np.nan_to_num(R_tmp[superSpecial_positions]) )
    
    Ss[n,0] = np.mean( np.nan_to_num(S_tmp) )
    Ss[n,1] = np.mean( np.nan_to_num(S_tmp[special_positions]) )
    Ss[n,2] = np.mean( np.nan_to_num(S_tmp[superSpecial_positions]) )
    

    # join values into vectors for measurements and predictions.
    m = np.concatenate([m_dict[i][:-30] for i in f]) # [:-30] because I didn't predict score for these residues 
    p = np.concatenate([p_dict[i] for i in f])

    ### Assuming that p value is the probability of type-I error, this area should be the equivalent
    corr_distribR = build_distribution(f,p_dict, m, n_iter=1000, corr_type='pearson') 
    corr_distribS = build_distribution(f,p_dict, m, n_iter=1000, corr_type='spearman') 
    
    # make it as subplots
    if n<20: plt.subplot(5,4,n+1)
    
    for shape1 in [0,1,2]: 
        plot = [True if shape1==1 and n<20 else False][0]
        p_valueR = calc_typeI_error(corr_distribR, Rs[n, shape1], plot=plot, bins=100)
        p_valueS = calc_typeI_error(corr_distribS, Ss[n, shape1], plot=False, bins=100)

        p_valuesR[n, shape1] = p_valueR
        p_valuesS[n, shape1] = p_valueS
    
    plt.title("cut_off={} and nreads={}\np_val={} ".format(FOLD_CHANGE_THRESHOLD, MINIMUM_READS, p_valueS));
    
plt.tight_layout()

norm = lambda arr1, arr2: np.vstack( [(arr1-np.min(arr1)) / (np.max(arr1)-np.min(arr1)), 
                                     (arr2-np.min(arr1)) / (np.max(arr1)-np.min(arr1))])
